Description: The Match.com for finding the perfect healthcare practitioner
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ABOUT The compatibility matching platform for patient-practitioner relationships PROBLEM Patients: 66% of Americans claim to not trust practitioners; the #1 contributor to non-compliance, and therefore, poor outcomes and frequent re-admissions. Currently, patients use search engines, databases or referrals to find practitioners, but this approach is still a "shot in the dark"​. Practitioners: A top pain point of practitioners is marketing their services, which require time, resources and expertise they don’t have. Currently, practitioners list and advertise their services and network when possible. These tactics are highly stressful and often unfruitful efforts.  SOLUTION Wellacopia is a compatibility matching platform that uses the proven concept of online dating to help patients find their ideal healthcare partner.  For practitioners, it is a comprehensive marketing platform that provides them with customizable profiles (i.e. advertisements), customer vetting (i.e. lead generation), and it is the only healthcare platform to allow practitioners to reach out to patients first because of the matching transparency on both sides (i.e. sales). ADVANTAGE Wellacopia is the 1st platform to use relationship preferences as criteria for matching in healthcare, plus we have made sure to incorporate the other necessary conveniences provided by existing platforms.  We understand the priority of compatibility and trust in successful healthcare. Our competitors were born out of the need to increase volumes (i.e. appointments). They are moving away from quality and focusing on quantity. Our platform goes beyond bulk numbers by integrating human experience with technological advancement.

Full Description: AVRA has been organized by a senior leadership team with decades of experience in medical research, innovation and development in the medical robotics field. The Company plans to meet the needs of the growing demand for practical medical robotic devices, focusing on the Dermatology field.   The Company believes that its team brings the necessary resources, including intellectual property, to develop and commercialize medical robotic devices, as well as in marketing, chain management, and the implementation of all other aspects of business operations.   The Company believes that progress in mechanical and software engineering has made possible lightweight and relatively inexpensive robotic devices for difficult procedures in various medical fields. AVRA and its management team have been active in the medical robotics space for many years, sponsoring, for example, www.allaboutroboticsurgery.com, an extensive reference data base for medical robotics news.   In Dermatology, technological improvements in motors, materials and in high resolution imaging allow for the use of robotic devices in treating damaged skin.   Presently, there are no such products commercially available for competition for these procedures.   AVRA is developing its prototype for robotic skin resurfacing employing an innovative helium plasma technology which the Company believes is superior to existing technologies such as Botox and CO2 lasers used for keratosis removal, the treatment of scarring and discoloration, and other skin problems that are often difficult to treat.

When friends pitch in together, you can give that awesome gift that may normally be outside of a single person's price range. We help you tap into the potential of social networks to make celebrating a special day seamless, social and fun. Other friends don’t need to spend the time deciding what to get. Description: Excalibur Engineering is engaged in the sale, rental, repair, and calibration of new and used test equipment for customers worldwide.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Excalibur was founded as a calibration laboratory specializing in acoustic and vibration calibration over 25 years ago by Christopher LaPlante. After being in business for a couple of years, and adding capabilities and people, we were approached time and again by customers wanting to buy, rent and trade in their test equipment, and they wanted to do it with someone they could trust, and someone who could support it, and someone who could help them make right decisions. So we started taking in customer trades, buying their excess, and renting specialized equipment that we were uniquely able to support, specifically sound and vibration measuring equipment. But as we expanded our calibration capabilities and expertise, it became clear that for us to support our customers totally, we had to add more lines and more services. About Excalibur Excalibur Engineering is first and foremost about customer service with a primary focus on the electronics industry.  We provide premium and innovative service solutions uniquely tailored to individual customer needs.  Our world-class, ISO 17025 accredited calibration lab provides a foundation for our suite of services:  Calibration, Repair, Sale and Rental of New and Used equipment.  Additionally we will help customers dispose of under-utilized test equipment assets through equipment buy-back programs.  We do business with customers worldwide from our headquarters in Irvine, California. Excalibur Engineering's extensive network of Manufacturer's Reps provides local customer engagement supported by our team of Regional Sales Managers.  Our deep understanding of test equipment supported by our calibration and repair facilities means we recommend the right test equipment, at the right price and with the assurance the equipment meets published specifications that will be supported.  Our history of providing a high degree of customer service contributes to generating long lasting customer relationships, repeat purchases, and referrals.

Description: Locations are in Cambridge, MN and Maplewood, MN.
Full Description: Locations are in Cambridge, MN and Maplewood, MN. Provide discounted gently used seasonal appropriate baby, kid, and maternity wear to the public at prices lower than retail, higher quality than thrift stores, on a twice a year (spring/summer and fall/winter sale): provide an outlet for families to sell their unwanted items, and replace those items as their children grow.This is on a consignment basis, allowing us to hold little to no permanent inventory. We provide a mecca of all things baby/kid and the customer base for our consignors to get a fair price. A better option than garage sales (hit or miss), ebay (shipping and fees), craigslist (strangers homes..), and dingy thrift stores (need I say more?). We reserve the right to refuse any item for any reason.  By providing these services only twice a year, we eliminate the need for a permanent store front  (even though the sales are held in the same general location)  Consignors pay a small fee to help cover facility rental and advertising costs. Consignors then may choose to volunteer, assisting in organizing, advertising, and clean-up. In exchange for this experience, they earn a higher percentage of commission from their sales, and recieve a pre-sale pass (allowing them to shop before the public). At the close of the sale, consignors remove their unsold items from the event.  Unclaimed items become our property. We work closely with local charities to donate most unclaimed items. There are prospective vendors all ready lining up to help cross promote. We also have several local child centers, health facilities, banks, schools, and home daycare facilities willing to distribute our informative postcards. Cutting down dramatically in postage, and hitting our direct market.
